---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'img-global', text: 'IMG Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'freelancer-needs', text: 'Freelancer-Specific Needs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'Remote Worker Insurance', href: '/best/remote-worker-insurance' },
  { title: 'Self-Employed Guide', href: '/insurance-for/self-employed' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Individual Plans', allianz: 'Yes', cigna: 'Yes', img: 'Yes' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', allianz: '€1M - €3M', cigna: 'Unlimited', img: '$1M - $8M' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing Handling', allianz: 'Flexible', cigna: 'Strict', img: 'Moderate' },
  { feature: 'Payment Flexibility', allianz: 'Monthly/Annual', cigna: 'Monthly/Annual', img: 'Annual' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', allianz: 'Best', cigna: 'Good', img: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Visa Letter', allianz: 'Yes', cigna: 'Yes', img: 'Yes' },
  { feature: 'Price Point', allianz: 'Mid-range', cigna: 'Premium', img: 'Budget-friendly' },
  { feature: 'Best For', allianz: 'Best value', cigna: 'Best service', img: 'Budget option' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 30', allianz: '$150-220/mo', cigna: '$250-380/mo', img: '$100-160/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 40', allianz: '$200-300/mo', cigna: '$350-500/mo', img: '$150-240/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 50', allianz: '$300-450/mo', cigna: '$500-750/mo', img: '$220-350/mo' },
  { profile: 'Self + Spouse, Age 35', allianz: '$350-500/mo', cigna: '$550-800/mo', img: '$250-400/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Allianz vs Cigna vs IMG: Best Insurance for Freelancers Abroad 2026"
  description="Compare health insurance for self-employed expats: Allianz Care, Cigna Global, and IMG Global. Individual plans, visa compliance, and pricing for freelancers."
  headline="Allianz vs Cigna vs IMG: Insurance for Freelancers Compared"
  subheadline="No employer coverage? Three insurers that work well for self-employed expats—from budget-friendly to premium protection."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Best balance of coverage and cost. Flexible on pre-existing. Monthly payment available. Strong mental health.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Service</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Premium coverage and service. Best app. Unlimited coverage. Worth it if you can afford it.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Budget Option</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">IMG Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Lowest prices for real health insurance. Good coverage limits. Solid choice for cost-conscious freelancers.</p>
      <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Freelancers don't have employer coverage—you're on your own. These three insurers all offer individual plans that work well for self-employed expats. Allianz provides the best value, Cigna the best service, and IMG the lowest prices.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Flexible Underwriting</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Mental Health</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care hits the sweet spot for freelancers: comprehensive coverage at 20-30% less than Cigna. They're more flexible on pre-existing conditions than competitors, offer monthly payment options, and have the best mental health coverage—important for those managing freelance stress.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Best value for comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li>Most flexible on pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>Monthly payment option available</li>
    <li>Best mental health benefits</li>
    <li>Visa compliance letters provided</li>
    <li>Strong European network</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>€3M coverage limit (vs Cigna's unlimited)</li>
    <li>App not as polished as Cigna</li>
    <li>Smaller direct billing network in some regions</li>
    <li>Claims processing slightly slower</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Freelancers who want comprehensive coverage without premium prices. Those with pre-existing conditions. Anyone prioritizing mental health coverage.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Service</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best App</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Unlimited Coverage</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global is the premium choice. Unlimited coverage, largest network, best app, fastest claims. As a freelancer without employer support, having the best service matters—you're managing everything yourself. Cigna makes it easier, but costs more.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Unlimited annual coverage</li>
    <li>Best mobile app in the industry</li>
    <li>Largest provider network (1.5M+)</li>
    <li>Fast claims processing</li>
    <li>Excellent customer service</li>
    <li>Monthly payment available</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive option</li>
    <li>Strict on pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>May be overkill for young, healthy freelancers</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Established freelancers with solid income. Those who value convenience and service. Anyone wanting the best coverage money can buy.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="img-global">IMG Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Budget-Friendly</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good Coverage</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Flexible Plans</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    IMG Global offers real health insurance at the lowest prices. Coverage limits up to $8M, flexible deductible options, and visa compliance—all at 30-40% less than Cigna. The trade-off is smaller network and more basic digital experience.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Lowest prices for comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li>Up to $8M coverage limits</li>
    <li>Flexible deductible options</li>
    <li>Visa compliance letters provided</li>
    <li>Good customer service</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions considered</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Annual payment typically required</li>
    <li>Smaller direct billing network</li>
    <li>App and digital experience basic</li>
    <li>Mental health coverage limited</li>
    <li>Claims processing slower</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Budget-conscious freelancers who want real coverage. Those in early freelance career with tighter cash flow. Anyone comfortable with reimbursement claims.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/img-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Freelancer Options"
    description="Get personalized quotes from all three. Consider your budget, health needs, and where you'll be working."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    As a freelancer, you're paying the full premium yourself—no employer contribution. The price differences are significant: IMG can be 40-50% cheaper than Cigna for similar coverage levels.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for comprehensive plans excluding US coverage. Prices vary based on age, health, location, and selected deductibles.
  </p>

  <h2 id="freelancer-needs">What Freelancers Need to Consider</h2>

  <h3>Visa Compliance</h3>
  <p>
    Many countries require health insurance for freelancer visas (Digital Nomad Visas, Freelancer Visas, etc.). All three provide:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Official insurance certificates for visa applications</li>
    <li>Proof of coverage letters</li>
    <li>Coverage that meets most visa requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Income Fluctuation</h3>
  <p>
    Freelance income varies. Consider:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Monthly payment spreads cost, moratorium option skips medical questions</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Monthly payment available, best service when you need it</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> Annual payment typical, but lowest overall cost</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Mental Health</h3>
  <p>
    Freelancing can be stressful and isolating. Mental health coverage matters:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Best—up to 50 therapy sessions/year, flexible on history</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Good—20-30 sessions, strict on prior history</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> Limited—basic coverage, fewer sessions</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Tax Deductibility</h3>
  <p>
    Health insurance premiums are often tax-deductible for self-employed individuals. Check your country's rules. Keep all receipts and payment records.
  </p>

  <h3>No Gap in Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Don't let coverage lapse between plans. Pre-existing condition rules reset with gaps. Maintain continuous coverage, especially as a freelancer without employer safety nets.
  </p>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want the best balance of coverage and price</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Prioritize mental health coverage</li>
        <li>Need monthly payment flexibility</li>
        <li>Work primarily in Europe</li>
        <li>Want moratorium underwriting option</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Have stable, higher income</li>
        <li>Want the best app and service</li>
        <li>Need unlimited coverage</li>
        <li>Value hassle-free claims</li>
        <li>Prefer direct billing everywhere</li>
        <li>Are healthy and want to stay that way</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose IMG Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are on a tight budget</li>
        <li>Are early in your freelance career</li>
        <li>Are young and healthy</li>
        <li>Can handle reimbursement claims</li>
        <li>Want real coverage at lowest cost</li>
        <li>Don't need extensive mental health coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Do I need international insurance as a freelancer?</h3>
  <p>
    If you're working abroad, yes. Local insurance may work if you're staying in one country permanently, but international insurance provides flexibility to move, travel, and get treatment anywhere. Most freelancer visas also require it.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I deduct health insurance on my taxes?</h3>
  <p>
    In many countries, yes. Self-employed individuals can often deduct health insurance premiums as a business expense. Check with a tax professional for your specific situation and country.
  </p>

  <h3>What if my income drops and I can't afford premiums?</h3>
  <p>
    Don't let coverage lapse—pre-existing conditions won't be covered if you restart later. Options: increase deductible to lower premium, switch to a cheaper plan, or use SafetyWing as a temporary bridge (though it's travel medical, not health insurance).
  </p>

  <h3>Do these plans work for digital nomad visas?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, all three meet most digital nomad visa requirements. However, some countries (like Portugal, Spain) have specific requirements. Check your specific visa's insurance requirements before purchasing.
  </p>

  <h3>What about liability insurance for my freelance work?</h3>
  <p>
    These are health insurance plans—they don't cover professional liability. If you need business insurance (errors & omissions, general liability), you'll need separate coverage from a business insurer.
  </p>

  <h3>Can my spouse/partner be on my plan?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, all three allow you to add dependents. You don't need to be married in most cases—domestic partners can usually be added. Premiums increase but less than buying two separate individual plans.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. As a freelancer, your insurance needs depend on your specific situation, location, and visa requirements. Verify coverage terms directly with each insurer before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
